OL,6,FMeanwhile, the Environment Agency has
OL,7,Freceived a record #189 million to
OL,8,Fsupport hundreds of enforcement
OL,9,Foffices for inspections and
OL,10,Fprosecutions, with fines from
OL,11,Fcompanies footing the increase in
OL,12,Ffunding.
OL,14,FMinisters hopes this will help to
OL,15,Freach its newly announced targets on
OL,16,Fsewage pollution, which can cause harm
OL,17,Fto swimmers, loss of aquatic live and
OL,18,Fdestruction to ecosystems.
